{
  "texts": [
    "75 The 72 This indicates another negligence element to the product liability standard, see Wuyts (2014, 16-17).",
    "73 For products requiring certification, \"some producers have argued that their product can no longer be defective once it has been authorised by the competent administrative body\" (Wuyts, 2014, 19) This argument has been rejected in e.g.",
    "Spain and Belgium.",
    "However, \"These standards clearly differ from the defence provided in art 7(d), which precludes complaint only if the defectiveness arises from a mandatory rule that completely deprives the producer of any discretion.\"",
    "(Wuyts, 2014, 19)."
  ]
}